  <div id=crumb><strong><a href="http://www.sfocp.com/html/san-francisco-suite-discount-hotel.asp">San Francisco Hotel Accomodations </a></strong> <img src="../images/bullet.gif" width="7" height="11" hspace="3" border="0"><a href="#1" class=anchor> Reasons to Stay</a>  <img src="../images/dots.gif" width="1" height="9" hspace="4"><a href="#2" class=anchor> </a></a><a href="#2" class=anchor>Room Details</a><a name="top" id="top"></a></div>
  <strong></strong>
  <p><strong><a href="http://www.sfocp.com/html/best-deal-san-francisco-hotel.asp"><img src="../images/manager-special2.jpg" alt="San Francisco Airport Hotel, Manager's Special" width="200" height="63" hspace="5" border="0" align="right"></a>Rooms by the Bay.</strong> Having recently completed a $23M renovation, the Crowne Plaza San Francisco International Airport features 309 splendidly remodeled hotel guest rooms, including 10 luxury suites as well as the Plaza Suite on the top floor. <br>
 <br>
 We also offer nonsmoking floors and handicap accessible guest rooms. All our unique hotel rooms offer an inviting, contemporary ambiance through the use of warm light ochre and green hues accented with maple furnishings. <br>
 <br><img src="../images/acco1_sm.jpg" align="right" hspace="8">
 The bathroom has a cantilevered glass shelf over the granite vanity, with a sleek stainless steel and opaque glass sconce to illuminate the room. </p>
         <p>Whether you are traveling for business or recreation, our well-appointed hotel rooms and suites provide an array of modern, lifestyle-enhancing amenities, including air conditioning, 25-inch television, cable, Nintendo, in-room movies, comfortable chair with ottoman, two dual-line phones (one with speakerphone) and high-speed internet. A large work desk with an ergonomic chair makes work away from the office easy and comfortable. The Third floor is a designated smoking floor. <a href="#1" class= milestone1>[Top]</a></p>
         <div class="break2"><img src="http://www.sfocp.com/images/pix.gif" width="1" height="1"></div>

  <h1><a name="1"></a>Bay Area Hotel, Reasons to Stay</h1>
  <table width="175" border="0" align="right" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0" class=cr1>
           <tr>
             <td><ul>
                 <li><a href="#11" class=milestone1>Club level </a></li>
                 <li><a href="#12" class=milestone1>Handicap Accessible Rooms &amp; Suites</a></li>
                 <li><a href="#13" class=milestone1> Pet Friendly Hotel </a><a href="#15" class=milestone1></a></li>
                 </ul></td>
           </tr>
  </table>
  <p><strong><a></a>Not So Standard Rooms. </strong> Our Standard Rooms offer a choice of king, queen or two double beds, a work desk with an ergonomic chair and a comfortable chair with ottoman, plus all our deluxe amenities. Smoking and non-smoking are available. </p>
  <p><strong> <a name="11" id="11"></a>Club Level. </strong>Our two Club Level floors offer the discerning traveler exclusive accommodations and services for a more luxurious stay. Located on the 9th and 10th floors of the hotel, Club Level rooms are only accessible via key  and offer additional upgraded hotel amenities.</p>
  <p>Complimentary continental breakfast and evening hors d'oeuvres (Monday through Friday) are served in the Club Lounge, located on the 10th floor. </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Executive Rooms</strong>. Executive rooms offer a choice of king, queen or two double beds, complimentary high-speed internet, and deluxe amenities for working or unwinding. <strong></strong></li>
  </ul>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Club Suites. </strong>Each of our 10 spacious suites includes a parlor room, complete with a work area, television, comfortable chair and sofa bed couch.<strong></strong></li>
  </ul>
 
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Plaza Suite.</strong> Located on the top floor of the hotel, our elegant one-bedroom suite includes a separate seating and dining area (for up to six people), and features a beautiful view of San Francisco Bay. <strong> </strong><a href="#1" class= milestone1>[Top]</a>

  </li>
  </ul><p><strong><a name="12" id="12"></a>Handicap Accessible Rooms &amp; Suites </strong></p>
  <p>To accommodate our physically-challenged and hearing-impaired guests, we offer several accessible rooms and suites, some featuring roll-in showers, grab bars, transfer shower seats, hand-held showers, lower door viewers, and closet rods and hangers. Hearing impaired hospitality kits, including test telephones, decoders and visual alarms are available by request.</p>
  <p>We provide 10 wheelchair-accessible rooms - eight with tubs, two with roll-in showers &ndash; and eight hearing-impaired guest rooms. Two suites features roll-in showers. Nine ADA parking spaces are available. <a href="#1" class= milestone1>[Top]</a>
  </p>
  <p><strong><a name="13" id="13"></a>Bay Area Hotel, Pets Are Guests Too </strong></p><img src="../images/acco2_pet_sm.jpg" align="right" hspace="8">
  <p>We welcome your pets with open arms and treats. Our hotel has a selection of pet-friendly rooms that are fully sanitized and ionized from previous guests. Our four-legged guests will enjoy a VIP &quot;pet turndown service&quot; and a Pet Menu on the In-Room Dining Menu, offering a selection of premium dog and cat food, and a complimentary bottle of water. </p>
  <p>Simply let us know you are bringing Fido or Fifi, and a special pet basket will be delivered and placed pet-level on the floor in your room or suite. Turn down service includes a yummy selection of doggie and kitty treats, pet chews and toys artfully presented in a gift basket. The hotel also provides &ldquo;poop&rdquo; bags for the owner to take care of the pet&rsquo;s business when they are out walking. The hotel requires a $100 refundable pet deposit. </p>
  The hotel is adjacent to Bay Side Sports Park, where leashed dogs are allowed on a trail that follows San Francisco Bay for miles. A three-minute walk with your pup, Burlingame Dog Park has<strong></strong>a special area for leash-free enjoyment from 6 a.m. to 9 p.m.
  <a href="#1" class= milestone1> [Top]</a>  <BR><BR>
